
Device List for the I50 and the XPs
====================================


I50
---

The I50 has an Analog Devices AD9887a analog-to-digital converter, 
an Integrated Device Technology ID18125 FIFO on the TX (Version DA)
board, and an Analog Devices AD9852 digital synthesizer on the RX
board. The AD9887a and ID18125 are accessed through the I2C bus 
implemented in the FPGA. The AD9852 is accessed through BAR2 on the
PCI bus. All 3 devices are supported in the driver.

XP100/200/220
-------------

The XPs have an PLX9056 PCI interface controller, an Analog Devices
AD9852 digital synthesizer, two NXP PCA9555 I2C I/O extenders, one 
Asaki Kasei Microelectronics AK4683AD and one AK4683AA audio codec, 
one Texas Instruments PCA9545 I2C switch, one Analog Devices AD9888 
analog-to-digital converter, two Silicon Image SiI1178 DVI transmitters, 
two DDRs and one 24LC01B EEPROM on the video board. There is also an 
LM63 temperature sensor on XP200/XP220 boards, and one PCA9555, one 
PCA9545 and one 24LC01B on the Personality Module (PM). 

The Ad9852 is access through BAR2 on the PCI bus.  

The PLX9056 controller is accessed through BAR3 on the PCI bus. 
There are driver routines for this.  All others XP devices are I2C 
devices they are accessed using user-space functions.

