In addition, both the I50 and the XP has the capability to read the
Enhanced Display Identification Data (EDID) on the displays connected 
on the output DVI port. The XP also has an EEPROM that can be programmed 
with EDID data for hosts connected to the input DVI port, a CDCE706, a
CDCE906 PLL synthesizer EEPROM and a configuration EEPROM for the NXP1520 
USB hub controller on the board. 

